AGI - He waited for a heir for 70 years before climbing on the throne >. On the death of her mother, Queen Elisabeth II, was crowned, exactly a year ago, but after a few months, she knew she had a cancer > and had to slow down, indeed stop her public commitments and keep behind the scenes only some of the official ones (for example weekly hearings with the Prime Minister). This was the first year on the throne of King Charles III celebrating the anniversary of the coronation, his and Queen Camilla, which took place on May 6, 2023 at Westminster Abbey.
&nbsp;
There is no sumptuous event >. And we do not know where the king and the queen will celebrate. At noon, however, the Royal Horse Artillery shot 41 gunshots from Green Park, and an hour later, at 13, the Honorable Artillery Company shot 62 more from the Tower of London. The king and the queen spent the weekend in Highgrove, probably the least royal of their residences, but the place that is more expensive to the king, the house that built in his image and that has always been his 'good retire'. Today there will be no great clamor that accompanied the coronation: is a day spent in private, > perhaps with the possibility to reflect on what year it was.
&nbsp;
The contrast could not be more evident, as pointed out by an 'insider': "Carrosses, crowns and madness over cancer." Cancer was discovered during a prostate routine operation, but it is not known what form it is (although it should not be prostate cancer). Since then, the king has been treated as an outpatient. Carlo continues to work; Indefensively, he says who is close to him. In these weeks, he wanted continuous updates on the work of the Foundations that are titled to him; and when last Tuesday he resumed his public commitments, after three months of pause, symbolically visited a center specialized in cancer care: appeared relaxed and smiling, he narrowed many hands and spoke with health professionals and patients but admitted that it was hard to learn the news of his illness.
&nbsp;
Almost a drink for a man who, throughout his life, between macrobiotic and biological foods and alternative cures, had made healthy lifestyle a line of conduct >.&nbsp; Now, the sources of the Palace tell that he is decided to use his disease to influence those who are sick like him >, encourage them and indeed spread the awareness that cancer beats better if soon diagnosed. We don't know practically anything about his illness, but doctors said "sufficiently satisfied" and watch over his recovery of public commitments, taking care that his agenda is not too heavy. The British newspaper The Times revealed that the king writes personal letters to his friends informing them of his state of health: admits that his condition is "a little unconscious", but he also tells his "determination" to defeat the disease and get back in motion.
&nbsp;
In the coming months there are important events and it is not yet clear whether Carlo will take part: the parade to celebrate the birthday of the monarch, Trooping the Colour, the commemoration of the Allied landing in Normandy 80 years ago, in June the arrival in London is also previewed of the emperors of Japan. The agenda remains reserved and any public appearance of the king will be announced with short notice, only after the 'free way' of doctors. Meanwhile, the image chosen to commemorate the first year from the coronation reveals a message: He portrays the king, of course, but next door is Camilla; and he is the queen who looks secure towards the camera, while he stares at her lovingly. A tribute to the role that, in these weeks, has played in public the queen, but perhaps also a tribute to the couple, who is also facing this new challenge.
&nbsp;
The family for the king is exceptionally important. The past year also brought news of the Princess of Wales' disease, Kate, also she has been out of the public scene for months: and remains the open wound with the Dukes of Sussex. On Wednesday, Prince Harry - whose eldest son Archie is five years old - will attend a ceremony at St Paul's Cathedral which marks the ten years of his Invictus Games. More or less at the same time, and not too far, the king should attend the first garden party of Buckingham Palace in the summer. With Harry there will not be Meghan, > the American wife who led him to live overseas, and who will meet him only at a later stage of his tour, when he will be in Nigeria. And who knows if the two, father and son, during the stay in London of the rebel ramp, will meet.&nbsp;

